    33	
    34	## Change Summary
    35	
    36	- `eden-git` now ships an `Integrator` that composes `GitRepo` with a
    37	  `Store` to promote `success` trials to canonical `trial/*` commits.
    38	  Order of operations: write commit object → `create_ref` (CAS) →
    39	  `store.integrate_trial`; compensating `delete_ref` on store-side
    40	  failure; `AtomicityViolation` if the compensating delete also fails.
    41	- §2 preconditions (`status == success`, `commit_sha` reachable from
    42	  `branch` tip), §1.4 reachability against declared `parent_commits`,
    43	  and §2 metrics validity are all enforced up front. Metrics
    44	  validation routes through the new public `Store.validate_metrics`
    45	  method.
    46	- §5.3 idempotency is verified end-to-end: second call on an already-
    47	  promoted trial re-derives the manifest bytes, re-constructs the
    48	  expected squash tree from the worker tip, and compares to the
    49	  committed artifacts; `CorruptIntegrationState` on any mismatch.
    50	- Eval-manifest bytes are deterministic (sorted keys, `indent=2`,
    51	  trailing newline) to make the §5.3 re-derivation stable.
    52	- The `eden-dispatch` driver now accepts `integrate_trial:
    53	  Callable[[str], object]` (typically `Integrator.integrate`)
    54	  instead of the Phase 5 placeholder `integrator_commit_factory`.
    55	- Spec §3.4 was tightened to make the post-promotion reading of the
    56	  cross-artifact invariant explicit, and a design note at
    57	  `spec/v0/design-notes/integrator-atomicity.md` captures the full
    58	  rationale and alternatives. This unblocked convergence of the plan
    59	  review after three rounds where codex kept flagging the plan-local
    60	  interpretation.
    61	- All 336 tests pass; ruff and pyright are clean; markdownlint-cli2
    62	  is clean; `scripts/spec-xref-check.py` resolves all 240 §-refs.
    63	
    64	## Review Status
    65	
    66	### Round 0 — findings addressed
    67	
    68	- **Bug — §5.3 replay after work/* pruning.** Fixed in
    69	  `integrator.py::_check_idempotent`. The manifest-bytes check no
    70	  longer depends on the worker commit being alive — it now reads
    71	  the committed trial commit's tree and manifest blob directly.
    72	  The tree-shape re-verification (§3.2 invariant) is now
    73	  conditional on `commit_exists(trial.commit_sha)` being true, since
    74	  §1.3 explicitly permits work/* cleanup. New regression test
    75	  `TestIdempotentReplayAfterWorkerPruned` runs `git gc
    76	  --prune=now` between integrations and asserts the second call is
    77	  a no-op.
    78	- **Bug — non-finite floats in metrics / manifest JSON.** Fixed in
    79	  two layers: `_base.py::_validate_metrics` now rejects non-finite
    80	  floats for `real` metrics via `math.isfinite()`; `_manifest.py`
    81	  sets `allow_nan=False` on `json.dumps` as defense in depth. New
    82	  test `TestNonFiniteMetricsRejected::test_nan_metric_rejected_at_integration`
    83	  seeds a trial with `float("nan")` and asserts
    84	  `NotReadyForIntegration`.
    85	- **Risk — dispatch → real integrator coverage gap.** Fixed by
    86	  `test_end_to_end_with_real_integrator` in
    87	  `eden-dispatch/tests/test_end_to_end.py`. The test builds a real
    88	  `GitRepo` in `tmp_path`, pre-creates three `work/*` branches,
    89	  seeds the scripted implementer to return the real SHAs/branches,
    90	  wires `Integrator.integrate` into `run_experiment`, and asserts
    91	  the `trial/*` refs exist, the subject lines match §3.3, and the
    92	  `trial.integrated` events land.
    93	
    94	All 339 tests pass. ruff / pyright / markdownlint / spec-xref clean.
    95	
    96	### Round 1 — awaiting review.

