**Findings**
- Bug — [integrator.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py:300), [integrator.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py:310): the new §1.3-pruned replay path now accepts an already-integrated trial without proving the §3.2 tree invariant. If `trial.commit_sha` has been pruned, `_check_idempotent()` skips `_require_squash_tree_matches()` and treats matching manifest bytes as sufficient. That lets a corrupted `trial/*` commit with extra paths pass as `already_integrated=True`. I reproduced this by rewriting the stored/ref commit to a tree with an extra file but the same `eval.json`, deleting `work/*`, running `git gc --prune=now`, and calling `integrate()` again; it was accepted as a no-op. Per §5.3, the no-op path is only valid when the recorded commit’s tree still satisfies §3.2. Fix by either persisting enough data at promotion time to re-verify tree shape after pruning, or by raising `CorruptIntegrationState` when the worker commit is gone and the §3.2 check cannot be completed. A regression test should be added alongside [test_integrator.py](/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-git/tests/test_integrator.py:853).

**Overall Assessment**
Plan adherence is otherwise improved: the non-finite-metrics bug is fixed cleanly, `allow_nan=False` is a good backstop, and the real dispatch-to-integrator end-to-end coverage is now present. On the five review axes: plan adherence, integration, robustness, and code quality are in good shape, but correctness still has the replay-hole above, so I would not sign this off yet.
